-- Indian Banks Seek to Refinance Airline Debt to Protect Loans, Mint Reports
-- Rakteem Katakey
-- 2010-06-28T02:07:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/indian-banks-seek-to-refinance-airline-debt-to-protect-loans-mint-reports.html

          
          
             Indian lenders, including State Bank
of India, are seeking to refinance airline debts to protect
their loans, the Mint newspaper reported, citing a banker it
didn’t identify.  
 India’s three biggest airlines, Air India, Jet Airways
(India) Ltd. and Kingfisher Airlines Ltd. have a combined $10
billion debt, according to the newspaper.  
